<article>
    <h1>SCO Live Con&#xAD;cert &#x2013; Essence Of SCO</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200911/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-11"><time>2020-09-11</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The Singapore Chi­nese Orches­tra (SCO) re­turns with its first con­cert with a live au­di­ence since the pan­demic, which will fea­ture well-loved clas­sics and be led by mu­sic di­rec­tor Tsung Yeh. It will kick off with an en­er­getic piece, Cel­e­bra­tion Over­ture, fol­lowed by an adap­ta­tion of the con­tem­pla­tive erhu clas­sic, Reflection Of The Moon On Erquan. The mood will then be lifted with a piece ti­tled Jas­mine, a flower that rep­re­sents pos­i­tiv­ity and pu­rity. The con­cert will end with The Ce­les­tial Web, to show the unity of peo­ple in these try­ing times.</p>
    <p>WHERE: SCO Con­cert Hall, Singapore Con­fer­ence Hall, 7 Shen­ton Way</p>
    <p>MRT: Raf­fles Place WHEN: To­day, 8pm (for in­vited guests only; oth­ers can tune in at SCO’s Face­book page) & to­mor­row, 3pm (lim­ited tick­ets are avail­able for the pub­lic).</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: Free INFO: sco.com.sg</p>


